The sociology of education is the study of how public institutions and individual experiences affect education and its outcomes.he Political Arithmetic tradition within the sociology of education began with Hogben (1938) and denotes a tradition of politically critical quantitative research dealing with social inequalities, especially those generated by social stratification (Heath 2000).
